
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ymbk-idr-bgp-eotr-policy-02.txt'>
    <title>"Route Leak Detection and Filtering using Roles in Update and Open messages", Alexander Azimov, Eugene Bogomazov, Randy Bush, Keyur Patel</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ymbk-idr-bgp-eotr-policy-02.txt</link>
    <description>[draft-ietf-idr-bgp-open-policy] defines a BGP OPEN capability and consequent route marking which enforces a valley-free peering relationship.  This document defines an eOTC (external Only To Customer) transitive BGP attribute which propagates the specific marking to automatically detect route leaks.  The goal is to allow a distant AS to determine a violation of valley-free peering.</description>
    <dc:date>2018-03-18T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
